signal.name: CCM_PMIC_READY
signal.description: Signal coming from PMIC to indicate that the voltage started to change as result of change in pmic_stby_req.

signal.name: CCM_PMIC_STBY_REQ
signal.description: Goes to PMIC_STBY_REQ pin, which notifies external power management IC to move from functional voltage to standby voltage.

padNet.name: VDD_ARM_CAP
padNet.description: Secondary Supply for the ARM Core's (internal regulator output - requires capacitor if internal regulator is used)

padNet.name: VDD_ARM_IN
padNet.description: Primary Supply for the ARM Core's Regulator

padNet.name: VDD_HIGH_CAP
padNet.description: Secondary Supply for the 2.5 V domain (internal regulator output - requires capacitor if internal regulator is used)

padNet.name: VDD_HIGH_IN
padNet.description: Primary Supply for the 2.5 V regulator

padNet.name: VDD_PU_CAP
padNet.description: Secondary Supply for the VPU and GPUs (internal regulator output - requires capacitor if internal regulator is used)

padNet.name: VDD_SNVS_CAP
padNet.description: Secondary Supply for the SNVS (internal regulator output - requires capacitor if internal regulator is used)

padNet.name: VDD_SNVS_IN
padNet.description: Primary Supply for the SNVS regulator

padNet.name: VDD_SOC_CAP
padNet.description: Secondary Supply for the SOC and PU (internal regulator output - requires capacitor if internal regulator is used)

padNet.name: VDD_SOC_IN
padNet.description: Primary Supply for the SOC and PU regulators

padNet.name: VDD_USB_CAP
padNet.description: Secondary Supply for the 3 V domain (internal regulator output - requires capacitor if internal regulator is used)

muxField.name: SION
muxField.description: Force the selected mux mode Input path no matter of MUX_MODE functionality.

muxFieldValue.name: DISABLED
muxFieldValue.description: Input Path is determined by functionality of the selected mux mode (regular).

muxField.name: MUX_MODE
muxField.description: Select iomux modes to be used for pad.

muxField.name: DAISY
muxField.description: Selecting Pads Involved in Daisy Chain.

padFieldValue.name: LPDDR2
padFieldValue.description: LPDDR2 mode (240 Ohm driver unit calibration, 240, 120, 80, 60, 48, 40, 32 Ohm drive strengths at 1.2V)

padFieldValue.name: DDR3
padFieldValue.description: DDR3 mode (240 Ohm driver unit calibration, 240, 120, 80, 60, 48, 40, 32 Ohm drive strengths at 1.5V)

padFieldValue.name: 1P2V_IO
padFieldValue.description: 1.2V I/O interfaces including USB HSIC. Provides calibrated drive strengths for signals ranging from 1.0V up to 1.3V.

padFieldValue.name: 1P5V_IO
padFieldValue.description: 1.5V I/O interfaces. Provides calibrated drive strengths for signals ranging from 1.3V to 2.5V.

padField.name: ODE
padField.description: Enables open drain of the pin.
